window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Winter has passed and the world returns to life once more. Spring brings with it new life, new opportunity, and new problems.</p> <p>With the pass having thawed, word reaches the members of the Ivory Spear tribe in their hideout at Silverstone valley. The baron that the village owes its allegiance to is moving troops around. Troops are camping in the vicinity of the nearby town of Amberpost.</p> <p>That alone would be stressful enough, but what they had learned from the elven envoys hangs heavy over Koda’s mind, as does the weight of trying to find and connect with the beast that hides within his bloodline.</p> <p>So once more, Koda and his mates must travel out into the plains, to find out what the baron’s forces are doing, and to see if the elves threats had any truth to them. Or if they were just that: threats.</p> <p>Only the gods know what Koda will find to the south, and only one of those is on his side at the moment.</p>"; 
